FT  14 JUN 93 / Letter: Predictions on share prices, please
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr GORDON MITCHELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, The improvement to the FT weather service is greatly welcomed.
Particularly useful are the forecast temperatures for the day of publication
in the leading centres of the world. Your previous service giving
temperatures at noon on the previous day was, after all, of interest to just
a few time travellers.
Perhaps the time is now right to extend this logic to your excellent London
Share Service. The previous day's figures are, after all, an esoteric
interest. The value of your newspaper would be immeasurably increased, for
the general reader, by the inclusion of forecast share prices at noon on the
day publication.
No doubt, the actuaries you use for your share indices could easily cope
with such a short-term forecast.
Gordon Mitchell,
146 Manor Green Road,
Epsom, Surrey KT19 8LL
</TEXT>
