FT  14 JUN 93 / Pension members 'denied voice'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NEARLY HALF of the smaller pension schemes for British companies give their
members no say in the appointment of trustees, a survey released today
shows.
Nearly two fifths of schemes rely on circulating only summarised accounts to
members and a quarter provide accounts only if specifically requested. The
details come in a survey of 67 pension schemes with assets of Pounds 1m to
Pounds 50m produced by accountants Clark Whitehill.
