FT  14 JUN 93 / World News in Brief: Grand National inquiry
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A Jockey Club inquiry into this year's Grand National steeplechase, which
was declared void after two false starts, said flagman Ken Evans failed to
wave a recall flag and that starter Keith Brown allowed horses to line up
too close to the starting tape.
