<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JUN 93 / London Stock Exchange: GEC at peak
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, JOEL KIBAZO and CHRISTINE BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Recent buying of GEC, the UK's flagship electronics group, gathered momentum
yesterday, driving the share price up to a record 338p. Just before the
close of trading they came off the top to end a net 4 1/2 up at 337 1/2 p.
Turnover was a good 6.9m shares.
A hefty buying order, reportedly from a single large US institution, was
driving the stock higher yesterday. Electronics specialists said GEC was one
of only a handful of top quality UK stocks, mostly among the utilities,
offering above-average dividend growth and a strong balance sheet.
GEC is scheduled to announce preliminary results on June 30, and analysts
expect profits in the region of Pounds 870m, up more than 5 per cent and a 7
per cent increase in the dividend total.
