<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JUN 93 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Pepper market was steady in active trading, reports Man Producten, while
Far Eastern exporters, who are expecting smaller crops, were reluctant
sellers. Muntok white pepper, spot, was available at Dollars 1,900 a tonne,
with June/July at Dollars 1,800 and July/August at Dollars 1,825. White
supplies from Sarawak, Thailand, China and Brazil were off the market. Among
the black peppers Sarawak black label, spot, was on offer at Dollars 1,200 a
tonne and June/July at Dollars 1,100. Sarawak yellow label, spot, was
Dollars 1,250 a tonne and June/July Dollars 1,150. Brazilian grade 1,
June/July, was Dollars 1,085 a tonne. Indian MG1, spot, was Dollars 1,225 a
tonne and June, Dollars 1,100.
</TEXT>
