<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JUN 93 / International Company News: S&amp;P raises rating of Chase
Manhattan debt
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
STANDARD &amp; Poor's, the credit information agency, yesterday raised its
ratings on Chase Manhattan following the New York banking group's sale of
Dollars 649m of new shares, writes Martin Dickson.
S&amp;P raised the rating on Chase's senior debt from triple-B-plus to
single-A-minus. Two other agencies, Fitch and Duff &amp; Phelps, also raised
their ratings on the bank.
Chase announced on Thursday that its offering of 22m shares, first announced
in April, had been priced at Dollars 29.50 a share. That was substantially
below the Dollars 750m the bank hoped to raise in April.
</TEXT>
