<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Heron creditor threatens to challenge
refinancing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MAGGIE URRY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A CREDITOR of Heron, the property group headed by Mr Gerald Ronson, is
threatening to challenge the group's financial restructuring and has called
on other creditors to join the action.
An advertisement placed in yesterday's Financial Times was signed by a
company called First Eastern Developments. It said the documents Heron had
issued in connection with the refinancing omitted important information.
Heron said the advertisement 'would appear to have been placed on the
specific instructions' of Stratagem Development Corporation, which is suing
Heron over the development of a property in New York, claiming damages of
Dollars 22.25m (Pounds 14.4m).
Heron said that it and its advisers 'deny that there is any omission of
important information from the scheme document'. It said the document
contained all the information creditors needed to make an informed decision
and 'there is no question of Heron's banks receiving an 'inappropriate
preference'.'
Heron has denied the allegations Stratagem has made in its law suit and has
made counter claims.
The move adds to unhappiness among some of Heron's bondholders about the
refinancing. Heron has said that if the refinancing deal is not acc-epted
then it would be forced to start bankruptcy proceedings, leaving creditors
with less than they would obtain through the refinancing.
</TEXT>
